args:
The Dragonyule season has arrived! Holiday
preparations in the village near the Halidom
are in full swing, but a fiend attack ends with
all their goods purloined. The prince promises
the despondent townspeople a party in the
Halidom, then takes off after the thieves.
A snowy eve, granted by dragons—\nThe starlight glimmering ever bright...
O sea of stars! Shine ever radiant!\nGrant us this miraculous night!
Hoo-ee! It's nice and toasty in here!
I appreciate you two taking care of the\nshopping. What's the snow situation\nlooking like out there?
There's PILES of it! Oh, and you've gotta\nsee the village—it's suuuper sparkly.
Sparkly? Wait, like sparks? Fire?\nThe village is on fire?!
Figuratively, ya dope! Not literally.\nJust think about it for a sec—\nwhat's coming soon?
Hmm... It's sparkly...and something's\ncoming soon... Ah! Dragonyule!
Only the most fun day EVER!
I'm not terribly familiar with it myself.\nIt's one of the Ilian Church's holidays, yes?
I always thought it was a time when\nhumans threw a snow party of some sort.\nAre you saying there's more to it?
I guess it makes sense that dragons and\nsylvans wouldn't be familiar with it.
In commemoration of the day of Ilia's\nbirth, the dragons combined their\npower and filled the sky with stars.
Because of that, the day of Ilia's birth\nis called ＂the night of falling stars.＂
And the festival held to celebrate the\nday came to be called ＂Dragonyule.＂
Hey, some INTERESTING history for once!\nEr, but what do you do on Dragonyule?\nFun stuff, right? Please say fun stuff.
Ya know it! We chow down on all kinds\nof tasty grub, and also hang a buncha\ndecorations on the ol' Yuletree.
And beneath those Yuletrees,\nwe exchange gifts.
And why do you do that?
Well, when Ilia was born, it's said people\ngave each other commemorative gifts.
After that, it just became something of\na holiday tradition.
Wait. All you humans get FREE presents?!\nThat is SO not fair!
If ya think it ain't fair, what say ya join in\nand do a little gift swap of yer own?

I fear it might not be so easy as all that.
There are doubtless many cultural aspects
of gift-giving we would need to understand
first, lest we make some boorish error.
Indeed. While it sounds rather like fun,\nI think it might prove difficult for us.
A man just showed up at the castle saying\nthe town was attacked by fiends!
C'mon, everyone! We have to go help!
Whaaaat?! All the sparkly decorations and\nstuff are GONE!
There doesn't appear to be much damage,\nbut the decorations and gifts have most\ncertainly been purloined.
They were stolen by fiends, they were!\nThe monsters took anything and everything\nwhat had to do with Dragonyule!
What would a pack of fiends want with\nall of your Dragonyule decorations?
Hush, child! You should be giving thanks\nno one was hurt instead of caterwauling\nabout a missing tree.
B-but now we can't celebrate, and I wanna\ncelebrate, and...and...WAAAAAAH!
Easy, there. You can celebrate with us.
In that case, we'll just throw a Dragonyule\ncelebration for everyone at the Halidom!
Yep. And we'll track down the fiends\nand find your stolen decorations\nand gifts as well.
Once we do, we'll put everything in the\ncastle to keep it nice and safe.
So stop crying, okay? It's all going to be\nbetter soon.
...We're having a party in the castle now?
It's the least we can do for these people.\nPlus, it will give our sylvan and dragon\nfriends a chance to experience the holiday.
So this is for us as well?
It's for everyone, Cleo—I know I'm looking\nforward to it!
In that case, we gotta put up the biggest\nYuletree the world's ever seen!
Agreed. But first we need to deal with\nthe fiends who attacked the village\nand reclaim all of that stolen property.
They can't have gotten very far yet;\nlet's suss 'em out and shake 'em down!
We'll get back the stolen decorations and\nput up a Yuletree in the castle!
